        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36221",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you please provide me with:\r\n* What is being produced by the baseUrl() view helper\r\n* What you actually want it to produce\r\n* Indicate how you would call it to achieve these results.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-19T15:45:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T15:45:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36225",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nebiros",
                        "name": "nebiros",
                        "displayName": "Juan Felipe Alvarez Saldarriaga",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is my url: http:\/\/192.168.2.3\/MyProject\/public so when I print the baseUrl return I got this: \/MyProject\/public so, the base tag needs the entire url (with the domain part http:\/\/192.168.2.3\/MyProject\/public) maybe you can add an extra argument to get the domain part too.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nebiros",
                        "name": "nebiros",
                        "displayName": "Juan Felipe Alvarez Saldarriaga",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-19T16:49:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T16:49:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36325",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There are some difficulties with honoring this request.\r\n* Clearly the scheme needs to be returned as well, but what if the current page is under SSL, and the page you want to link to doesn't require SSL?\r\n* Should the port be included?\r\nThis looks like up to three additional arguments, all of them optional, which would make for a cumbersome API.\r\n\r\nMy thought is that it would be best to have a separate helper for generating the scheme + host + port portion of the URL, and using it in conjunction to the baseUrl() view helper:\r\n{code}\r\necho $this->hostName() . $this->baseUrl();\r\n{code}\r\nIf you would like to see this feature, please create a proposal for it to ensure we capture all the requirements.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T10:59:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T10:59:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36362",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nebiros",
                        "name": "nebiros",
                        "displayName": "Juan Felipe Alvarez Saldarriaga",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hum, you'r right too many arguments and it suck, I like the idea of a new helper maybe I'll sign the CLA ;), thanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nebiros",
                        "name": "nebiros",
                        "displayName": "Juan Felipe Alvarez Saldarriaga",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T13:50:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T13:50:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
